title: JI’s Naeem ur Rehman Khan wins PS-129 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamat-e-Islami’s (JI) Naeem ur Rehman Khan has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-129, Karachi Central-VIII, by securing 26,296 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muttahidda Qaumi Movement’s (MQM) Muaz Muqaddam, who bagged 20,296 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 31.73 %.
